---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Flamme Rouge Scoreboard">
  <section class="py-5">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Title & Intro -->
      <div class="text-center mb-5">
        <h1 class="mb-2">Flamme Rouge Scoreboard</h1>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2">
          A fan-built Flask web app for the Flamme Rouge board game that allows players to run multi-stage races with clean tracking of GC, sprints, and mountain classifications.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Overview & Live Link -->
      <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
          <h2 class="h5">Overview</h2>
          <p>
            The app lets users create a race, record stage results, and automatically compute general classification (GC), sprint, and mountain standings.
            You can define race stages, enter results, and continue multi-stage play using a generated race ID.
          </p>
          <p>
            Try it live:  
            <a href="https://flamme-rouge-app-gsdbg0cudsh7cpat.northeurope-01.azurewebsites.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              Launch the Flamme Rouge Scoreboard on Azure
            </a>.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
          <h2 class="h5">Tech & Tools</h2>
          <ul class="mb-0">
            <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Flask (Python), session management, Jinja2 templates</li>
            <li><strong>Database:</strong> PostgreSQL hosted on Azure for secure race/team data storage</li>
            <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> HTML/CSS, JavaScript for dynamic forms (e.g. entering results)</li>
            <li><strong>Deployment:</strong> Azure App Service</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Features -->
      <div class="mb-5">
        <h3 class="h5 mb-3">Key Features</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Multi-stage race creation and result tracking</li>
          <li>Automatic GC, sprint, and mountain classification scoring</li>
          <li>Optional advanced rules: point systems, assistant riders, time trials, “good day/bad day” modifiers</li>
          <li>Stage continuation via unique Race ID stored across sessions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Back to Projects -->
      <div class="text-center mt-5">
        <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary" href="/projects/">← Back to Projects</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
